CFItems.fullStatement: Welding Skills
Technical Welding
Understands basic TIG welding techniques and can perform simple welds under supervision.
Executes standard TIG welds independently, with occasional guidance for complex tasks.
Produces high-quality, precise welds on various metals and alloys, adhering to industry standards.
Innovates welding techniques, mentors others, and ensures exceptional quality in challenging projects.
Blueprint Reading
Recognizes basic symbols and layouts but requires assistance to interpret detailed blueprints.
Reads and follows standard blueprints with minimal guidance.
Accurately interprets complex blueprints and specifications to plan and execute welding tasks.
Identifies potential design issues and collaborates with engineers to optimize plans.
Attention to Detail
Identifies obvious errors but may overlook finer details in welds or materials.
Detects and corrects minor imperfections in welds with some oversight.
Consistently ensures welds meet exacting standards, with no errors or defects.
Anticipates and prevents potential issues, maintaining flawless quality control.
Business Process Skills
Lean Six Sigma Knowledge
Understands basic Lean and Six Sigma concepts (e.g., waste types, DMAIC).
Can participate in improvement projects and use tools like 5S, Fishbone, Pareto.
Leads CI projects using DMAIC or PDCA; capable of data-driven analysis.
Trains others in Lean Six Sigma; develops org-wide strategies; Green/Black Belt certified.
Problem Solving & Root Cause Analysis
Can identify problems and document them clearly.
Applies tools like 5 Whys or Ishikawa diagrams.
Facilitates cross-functional RCA sessions and develops corrective actions.
Develops systematic RCA approaches and mentors teams in advanced methods.
Process Mapping & Standardization
Able to follow documented processes.
Creates and interprets flowcharts, SIPOC, and value stream maps.
Leads process mapping workshops and standard work development.
Optimizes and re-engineers processes organization-wide.
Continuous Improvement Mindset
Data-Driven Decision Making
Cross-Functional Collaboration
Change Facilitation
